The beam that BATSCOUT had focused on the door has been shut off,
there are no other beams present in or around the door.

The two intrepid travelers are still standing at the end of a long
underground tunnel, the one that ran under the nearly frozen lake that
everyone saw from above. There is no sign of vents or air ducts or any
other modern convenience, even lights are absent, except for the one
that BATSCOUT is shining to illuminate the door.

The walls appear to be made of stone and rock carved out of the earth
itself. There is even an earthy smell to the place, occasionally
insects scuttle around now that BATSCOUT&#39;s light is here to illuminate
things.

There is no other way to go. Either they go through the door or they
go back the way they just came.

Red scanning beams focus on the black object that NIGHTSHIFT coughed
up. &quot;It would appear to be a hairball.&quot; BATSCOUT said in his soft
computerized voice. &quot;A hairball with stange unidentified electrical
componants.&quot; The scanning beam shuts off.

